All Implemented Interfaces:
Heartbeat, HeartbeatPipe, MemoryMonitorable, Pipe<TemporalObject<E>,TemporalObject<E>>, Node, Sink<TemporalObject<E>>, Source<TemporalObject<E>>, MetaDataManageable<Object,Object>, MetaDataProvider<CompositeMetaData<Object,Object>>
public class NestedTemporalWindow<E>
extends AbstractTemporalPipe<E,E>
implements MemoryMonitorable

An operator for continuous queries with time-based windows, for instance fixed and sliding windows. For use in nested queries, when two or more window operators occur on a path from a source to a sink. assumption: elements arrive at this operator with the specified time granularity

processObject

public void processObject(TemporalObject<E> tso,
                          int sourceID)
Description copied from class: AbstractPipe
This method has to be overwritten to process each incoming element. The transfer method has to be called inside this method to transfer the processing results to all subscribed sinks. Consequently, its execution is considered to be atomar.
